obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25858)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st April 2010, vide notification F. No. 3/6/2007-Jute, 30th March, 2010, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part I, sec. 2`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25858&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Jute Board Act,`
  line 2008.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25859)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25859&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint for the purpose of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the National Jute Board constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) "Council" means the Jute Manufactures Development Council established under section 3 of`
  line `the Jute Manufactures Development Council Act, 1983 (27 of 1983);`
  line
  line `(e) "Jute" means the plants of jute, kenaf and mesta;`
  line
  line `(f) "jute manufacture" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Jute Manufactures`
  line `Cess Act, 1983(28 of 1983);`
  line
  line `(g) "member" means a member of the Board and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "Society" means the National Centre for Jute Diversification, a society set up by the Central`
  line `Government in the Ministry of Textiles and registered under the Societies Registration Act,1860`
  line `(21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(k) "year" means the year commencing on the 1st day of April and ending on the 31st day of`
  line `March next following.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25860)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution and incorporation of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25860&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the appointed day, the Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute, for the purposes of this Act, a Board`
  line `to be called the National Jute Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Board shall be at Kolkata in the State of West Bengal or such other place as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify and the Board may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, establish offices or agencies at other places in or outside`
  line India.
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Secretary in charge of the ministry of the Central Government dealing with textiles, who`
  line `shall be the ex officio Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) three Members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected from among themselves by the`
  line `members of the House of the People and one from among themselves by the members of the Council`
  line `of States;`
  line
  line `(c) the Additional Secretary and Financial Adviser, Ministry of Textiles, Government of India,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Joint Secretary (Jute) in the Ministry of Textiles, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) two members of the rank of Joint Secretary to be nominated by the Central Government to`
  line `represent respectively the ministries of the Central Government dealing with--`
  line
  line `(i) agriculture, and`
  line
  line `(ii) food and public distribution;`
  line
  line `(f) three members to be nominated by the Central Government by rotation in the alphabetical`
  line `order to represent respectively the Governments of the States of Andhra Pradesh, Assam, Bihar,`
  line `Meghalaya, Orissa, Tripura and West Bengal; the nomination shall be from officials of the State`
  line `Government holding the rank of Secretary to the State Government and dealing with Jute or Textile`
  line matters;
  line
  line `(g) three members of jute farmers of which one from State of West Bengal and two from other`
  line `States on rotational basis to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) three members of jute workers of which one from State of West Bengal and two from other`
  line `States nominated by the Central Government on rotational basis;`
  line
  line `(i) two experts from the field of jute technology and related field to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(j) two members from the "micro enterprises", "small enterprises" and "medium enterprises"`
  line `dealing in jute industry to be nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, the expressions "medium enterprise", "micro`
  line `enterprise" and "small enterprise" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clause (g),`
  line `clause (h) and clause (m) of section 2 of the Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises Development Act,`
  line `2006 (27 of 2006);`
  line
  line `(k) two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the jute industry in the`
  line `organised sector;`
  line
  line `(l) two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the jute industry in the`
  line `decentralised sector;`
  line
  line `(m) two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the exporters of jute`
  line products;
  line
  line `(n) the Director, Indian Jute Industries Research Association, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(o) the Principal, Institute of Jute Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(p) the Director, National Institute of Research on Jute and Allied Fibre Technology, Kolkata,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(q) the Director, Central Research Institute for Jute and Allied Fibres, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(r) the Chairman and Managing Director, Jute Corporation of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(s) the Jute Commissioner, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(t) the Secretary, National Jute Board, who shall be the ex officio Member-Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of the members, other than the ex officio members, and the manner of filling`
  line `vacancies among, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, such members`
  line `shall be as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The office of members of the Board shall not disqualify its holder for being chosen as, or for`
  line `being a member of either House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of the Board, exercise and`
  line `discharge such powers and duties of the Board as may be assigned to him by the Board and such other`
  line `powers and duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The Board shall elect from among its members a Vice-Chairperson who shall exercise such of the`
  line `powers and perform such of the functions of the Chairperson as may be prescribed or as may be delegated`
  line `to him by the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(9) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such procedure in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be determined by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25861)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Secretary and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25861&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint the Secretary and such`
  line `other officers and employees as it considers necessary, for the efficient discharge of the functions of the`
  line `Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25862)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25862&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to promote the development of jute and`
  line `jute products by such measures as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, the Board may undertake measures`
  line to--
  line
  line `(i) evolve an integrated approach to jute cultivation in the matters of formulation of schemes,`
  line `extension work, implementation and evaluation of schemes aimed at increasing the yield of jute and`
  line `improving the quality thereon;`
  line
  line `(ii) promote production of better quality raw jute;`
  line
  line `(iii) enhance productivity of raw jute;`
  line
  line `(iv) promote or undertake arrangements for better marketing and stabilisation of the prices of raw`
  line jute;
  line
  line `(v) promote standardisation of raw jute and jute products;`
  line
  line `(vi) suggest norms of efficiency for jute industry with a view to eliminating waste, obtaining`
  line `optimum production, improving quality and reducing costs;`
  line
  line `(vii) propagate information useful to the growers of raw jute and manufacturers of jute products;`
  line
  line `(viii) promote and undertake measures for quality control of raw jute and jute products;`
  line
  line `(ix) assist and encourage studies and research for improvement of processing, quality, techniques`
  line `of grading and packaging of raw jute;`
  line
  line `(x) promote or undertake surveys or studies aimed at collection and formulation of statistics`
  line `regarding raw jute and jute products;`
  line
  line `(xi) promote standardisation of jute manufactures;`
  line
  line `(xii) promote the development of production of jute manufactures by increasing the efficiency`
  line `and productivity of the jute industry;`
  line
  line `(xiii) sponsor, assist, coordinate, encourage or undertake scientific, technological, economic and`
  line `marketing research pertaining to the jute sector;`
  line
  line `(xiv) maintain and improve existing markets and to develop new markets within the country and`
  line `outside for jute manufactures and to devise marketing strategies in consonance with the demand for`
  line `such manufactures in the domestic and international markets;`
  line
  line `(xv) sponsor, assist, coordinate or encourage scientific, technological and economic research in`
  line `the matters related to materials, equipment, methods of production, product development including`
  line `discovery and development of new materials, equipment and methods and improvements in those`
  line `already in use in the jute industry;`
  line
  line `(xvi) provide and create necessary infrastructural facilities and conditions conducive to the`
  line `development of diversified jute products by way of assisting the entrepreneurs, artisans, craftsman,`
  line `designers, manufacturers, exporters, non-Governmental agencies in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer of technology from research and development institutions and other`
  line `organisations in India and abroad;`
  line
  line `(b) providing support services to the entrepreneurs for the implementation of their`
  line `projects including technical guidance and training;`
  line
  line `(c) organising entrepreneurial development programmes;`
  line
  line `(d) planning and executing market promotion strategies including exhibitions,`
  line `demonstrations, media campaigns in India and abroad;`
  line
  line `(e) providing financial assistance by way of subsidy or seed capital;`
  line
  line `(f) providing a forum to the people engaged or interested in diversified jute products for`
  line `interacting with various national and international agencies, engaged in the jute and jute`
  line `textile sector;`
  line
  line `(xvii) organise workshops, conferences, lectures, seminars, refresher courses and set up study`
  line `groups and conduct training programmes for the purpose of promotion and development of jute and`
  line `jute products;`
  line
  line `(xviii) undertake research on jute seed to improve quality and to shorten the gestation period of`
  line `jute crop;`
  line
  line `(xix) incorporate measures for sustainable Human Resource Development of the jute sector and to`
  line `provide necessary funds for the same;`
  line
  line `(xx) modernisation of jute sector and technology development;`
  line
  line `(xxi) take steps to protect the interests of jute growers and workers and to promote their welfare`
  line `by improving their livelihood avenues;`
  line
  line `(xxii) secure better working conditions and provisions and improvement of amenities and`
  line `incentives for workers engaged in the jute industry;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) register jute growers and manufacturers on optional basis;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) collect statistics with regard to jute and jute products for compilation and publication;`
  line
  line `(xxv) subscribe to the share capital of or enter into any arrangement (whether by way of`
  line `partnership, joint venture or any other manner) with any other body corporate for the purpose of`
  line `promoting the jute sector or for promotion and marketing of jute and jute products in India and`
  line abroad.
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of the Board--`
  line
  line `(a) to advise the Central Government on all matters relating to the development of raw jute and`
  line `the jute industry, including import and export of jute and jute products;`
  line
  line `(b) to prepare and furnish reports relating to the jute sector as may be required by the Central`
  line `Government from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25863)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `The Council and Society to vest in Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25863&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, there shall be`
  line `transferred to, and vest in, the Board constituted under section 3, the Council and the Society.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council and the Society which is transferred to, and which vests in, the Board under subsection`
  line `(1) shall be deemed to include all assets, rights, powers, authorities and privileges and all property`
  line `movable and immovable, real or personal, corporeal or incorporeal, present or contingent, of whatever`
  line `nature and wheresoever situate, including lands, buildings, machinery, equipments, cash balances, capital,`
  line `reserves, reserve funds, investments, tenancies, leases and book debts and all other rights and interests`
  line `arising out of such property as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership or possession`
  line `or power of the Council, or as the case may be, the Society, whether within or outside India, all books of`
  line `account and documents relating thereto and shall also be deemed to include all borrowings, liabilities and`
  line `obligations of whatever kind then subsisting of the Society, or as the case may be, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25864)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `General effect of vesting of Council and Society in Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25864&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) All contracts, agreements and`
  line `working arrangements subsisting immediately before the appointed day and affecting the Council, or, as`
  line `the case may be, the Society shall, in so far as they relate to the Council, or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Society, cease to have effect or be enforceable against the Council, or, as the case may be, the Society and`
  line `shall be of as full force and effect against or in favour of the Board in which the Council and the Society`
  line `have vested by virtue of this Act and enforceable as fully and effectively as if, instead of the Council, or,`
  line `as the case may be, the Society, the Board had been named therein or had been a party thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Any proceeding, suit or cause of action pending or existing immediately before the appointed day`
  line `by or against the Council or the Society may, as from that day, be continued and enforced by or against`
  line `the Board in which it has vested by virtue of this Act, as it might have been enforced by or against the`
  line `Council or the Society if this Act had not been passed, and shall cease to be enforceable by or against the`
  line `Council or, as the case may be, the Society.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25865)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Licences, etc., to be deemed to have been granted to Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25865&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `With effect from the appointed`
  line `day, all licences, permits, quotas and exemptions, granted to the Council or the Society in connection with`
  line `the affairs and business of the Council, or, as the case may be, the Society, under any law for the time`
  line `being in force, shall be deemed to have been granted to the Board in which the Council and the Society`
  line `have vested by virtue of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25866)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Tax exemption or benefits to continue have effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25866&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any exemption from, or any`
  line `assessment with respect to, any tax has been granted or made or any benefit by way of set off or carry`
  line `forward, as the case may be, of any unabsorbed depreciation or investment allowance or other allowance`
  line `or loss has been extended or is available to the Council or the Society, under the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961), such exemption, assessment or benefit shall continue to have effect in relation to the Board`
  line `in which the Council and the Society have vested by virtue of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any payment made by the Council or the Society is exempted from deduction of tax at`
  line `source under any provision of the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961) the exemption from tax will continue`
  line `to be available as if the provisions of the said Act made applicable to the Council or the Society were`
  line `operative in relation to the Board in which the Council and the Society have vested by virtue of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The transfer and vesting of the Council or the Society in terms of section 6 shall not be construed`
  line `as a transfer within the meaning of the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961) for the purposes of capital`
  line gains.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25867)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Guarantee to be operative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25867&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any guarantee given for or in favour of the Council or the Society`
  line `with respect to any loan or lease finance shall continue to be operative in relation to the Board in which`
  line `the Council and the Society have vested by virtue of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25868)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provisions in respect of officers and other employees of Council and Society.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25868&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) Every`
  line `officer or other employee of the Council serving in its employment immediately before the appointed day`
  line `shall, in so far as such officer or other employee is employed in connection with the Council which has`
  line `vested in the Board by virtue of this Act, becomes, as from the appointed day, an officer, or, as the case`
  line `may be, other employee of the Board.`
  line
  line `(b) Every officer or other employee of the Society serving in its employment immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, in so far as such officer or other employee is employed in connection with the`
  line `Society which has vested in the Board by virtue of this Act, becomes, as from the appointed day, an`
  line `officer, or, as the case may be, other employee of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer or other employee of the Council or the Society who becomes an officer, or as the`
  line `case may be, other employee of the Board, as referred to in sub-section (1), shall hold his office or service`
  line `therein by the same tenure, at the same remuneration, upon the same terms and conditions, with the same`
  line `obligations and rights and privileges as to leave, insurance, superannuation scheme, provident fund, other`
  line `funds, retirement, pension, gratuity and other benefits as he would have held under the Council, or, as the`
  line `case may be, the Society, if it had not vested in the Board and shall continue to do so as an officer or other`
  line `employee, as the case may be, of the Board, or until the expiry of a period of one year from the appointed`
  line `day if such officer or other employee opts not to be the officer or other employee of the Board within such`
  line `period:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Board thinks it expedient to extend the period so fixed, it may extend the same up`
  line `to a maximum period of one year.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an officer or other employee of the Council or the Society opts under sub-section (2) not to`
  line `be in the employment or service of the Board in which the Council and the Society have vested, such`
  line `officer or other employee shall be deemed to have resigned from the respective cadre.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947(14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee of the`
  line `Council or the Society to the Board shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation`
  line `under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The officers and other employees who have retired before the appointed day from the service of`
  line `the Council or the Society and are entitled to any benefits, rights or privileges shall be entitled to receive`
  line `the same benefits, rights or privileges from the Board in which the Council and the Society have vested.`
  line
  line `(6) The trusts of the Provident Fund and Group Insurance and Superannuation Scheme of the Council`
  line `or the Society for the welfare of officers or employees would continue to discharge their functions in the`
  line `Board as was being done hitherto in the Council or the Society and tax exemption granted to Provident`
  line `Fund or Group Insurance and Superannuation Scheme would continue to be applied to the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) After the expiry of the period of one year, or the extended period, as referred to in sub-section (2),`
  line `all the officers and other employees transferred and appointed to the Board, other than those opting not to`
  line `be the officers or employees of the Board within such period, shall be governed by the rules and`
  line `regulations made by the Board in respect of the service conditions of the officers and other employees of`
  line `the said Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25869)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25869&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall, in the discharge of its functions and`
  line `duties under the relevant statute, be bound by the directions on questions of policy as the Central`
  line `Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25870)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Supersession of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25870&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central Government is of the opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) on account of grave emergency, the Board is unable to discharge the functions and duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Board has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the Central`
  line `Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or under`
  line `the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default, the financial position of the Board or the`
  line `administration of the Board has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Board for such period,`
  line `not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members of the Board shall, as from the date of supersession vacate their offices as`
  line such;
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of the relevant Act,`
  line `be exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central Government`
  line `may direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted, vest in`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may reconstitute the Board by a fresh appointment and in such`
  line `case any person or persons who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall not be`
  line `deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time, before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, take action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification to be issued under sub-section (1) and a full`
  line `report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action will be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25871)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25871&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law, in this behalf, make to the Board grants and loans of such sums`
  line `of money as that Government may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the Jute Board Fund and there shall be credited`
  line thereto--
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the Board by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Board from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) salary, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other employees of`
  line `the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions; and`
  line
  line `(c) expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25872)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25872&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare in such form and at such time during each financial year, as`
  line `may be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure`
  line `of the Board, and forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25873)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25873&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall prepare in such form and at such time, each financial year, as`
  line `may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial`
  line `year and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25874)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25874&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of the Board shall be maintained and audited in such manner`
  line `as may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed and the Board`
  line `shall furnish to the Central Government before such date, as may be prescribed, an audited copy of its`
  line `accounts, together with the auditor's report thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25875)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Laying of annual and auditor’s report before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25875&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `cause the annual report and auditor's report to be laid, as soon as may be after they are received, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25876)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25876&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, or the Board or any member of the Board, or any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Central Government or of the Board or any other person authorised by the Central`
  line `Government or the Board, for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act`
  line `or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25877)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Officers and employees of Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25877&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `All officers and employees of the`
  line `Board shall, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or`
  line `regulation made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25878)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25878&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office and other conditions of service of the members of the Board under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the Chairperson under sub-section (7) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and functions of the Vice-Chairperson under sub-section (8) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which, and the time at which, the Board shall prepare its budget under section`
  line 15;
  line
  line `(e) the form in which, and the time at which, the Board shall prepare its annual report under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the accounts of the Board shall be maintained and audited, and the date`
  line `before which the audited copy of the accounts may be furnished to the Central Government under`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be, or may be, made by the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25879)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25879&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act and the rules generally to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which the business of the Board shall be conducted under sub-section (9) of`
  line `section 3; and`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Secretary and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Board under section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25880)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25880&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is`
  line `in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25881)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25881&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (25882)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Amendment of Act 28 of 1983.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25882&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In the Jute Manufactures Cess Act, 1983,--`
  line
  line `(a) in section 3,--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words and figures "the Jute Manufactures Development Council`
  line `Act, 1983", the words and figures "the National Jute Board Act, 2008 (12 of 2009)" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), the words "and Salt" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(iii) in sub-section (4), the words "and Salt" shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(b) in section 4, for the words, brackets and figures "the Jute Manufactures Development Council,`
  line `from time to time, from out of such proceeds (after deducting the cost of collection which shall not`
  line `exceed four per cent. of such proceeds) such sums of money as it may think fit for being utilised for the`
  line `purposes of the Jute Manufactures Development Council Act, 1983 (27 of 1983), the words, brackets and`
  line `figures "the National Jute Board from time to time, from out of such proceeds (after deducting the cost of`
  line `collection which shall not exceed four per cent. of such proceeds) such sums of money as it may think fit`
  line `for being utilised for the purposes of the National Jute Board Act, 2008 (28 of 1983), shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (25883)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624&sectionId=25883&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00016_200912_1517807327624
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, the Jute Manufactures Development`
  line `Council Act, 1983 (27 of 1983) shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done or`
  line `taken under the Act so repealed shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
